The paper discusses prediction markets, which are commonly studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of agents influencing each other's beliefs is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes novel strategy-proof markets, which falls under the category of mechanism design (cs.EC).
